Content:
Education Review (ISSN1094-5296) is an open-access academic journal publishing reviews of books in the field of education. It was established in 1998 by Gene V. Glass and Nicholas Burbules (University of Illinois at UrbanaChampaign. The journal publishes peer-reviewed essay reviews and reviews of scholarly books. Reviews of books published in Spanish and Portuguese are also published. Reviews in English are edited by Glass and co-editor Melissa Cast-Brede (University of Nebraska at Omaha). Reviews in Spanish or Portuguese are edited by Gustavo Fischman (Arizona State University). Education Review publishes approximately 250 reviews each year. Starting in 2010, Education Review is published by the National Education Policy Center at the School of Education, University of Colorado at Boulder.
